article 1 Minerals and Plants
certain minerals are required by plants for normal growth and development.
	be required for 被什么需要
Even nitrogen, which is  gas in its elemental state, is normally absorbed from the soil as nitrate ions.
	nitrogen 氮
	in its elemental state 在它的元素状态
	nitrate ions 硝酸盐离子
Some soils are notoriously deficient in micro nutrients and are therefore unable to support most plant life.
	notoriously 众所周知地
	micro nutrients 微营养物
So called serpentine soil are deficient in calcium 
	serpentine soil蛇纹岩
chlorosis 变色病
chlorophyll 叶绿素
necrosis(isolated dead patched) 坏死（孤立的死斑）
anthocyanin formation花青素形成
deep red pigmentation 深红色斑点
stunted growth发育不良的生长
slender 细长的
phosphorus is mobilized to young growing tissue.磷被动员到新生长的组织中

article 2 the Origin of the pacific island People
The greater pacific region, traditionally called oceania consists of three cultural areas.
	pacific 大西洋的
	oceania 大洋洲
consist primarily of small scattered islands
	scattered 散射的;分散的
outsider外人
Many fanciful and mutually exclusive theories were devised
	fanciful 幻想的
	mutually exclusive互相驳斥的
	devise  想出；发明
Mant thoeries implicitly deprecated the navigational abilities and overall cultural creativity of pacific islanders.
	implictly含蓄地
	deprecate反对
drift on a balsa-log raft westward with the winds and currents across the pacific from south america to prove his theory.
	drift on 漂流
	balsa-log raft 轻质木筏
easter island复活节岛
taro 芋头
yarn 纱线
sugarane甘蔗
breadfruit面包果
sago西米

be settled by polynesians accidentally marooned after being lost and adrift, it seems reasonable that this feat was accomplished 
	maroon陷入困境
